11/05/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The European Commission's (EC) assessment of Montenegro's EU membership application will be completed by autumn, the EC Head of Delegation in Podgorica, Leopold Maurer, said on Monday (May 10th).
He pointed out that based on this opinion, EU leaders will decide by year end whether to offer candidate status.
Podgorica submitted its application in December and hopes to receive candidate status early in 2011.
(Antena M, Portal Analitika, Radio Free Europe - 10/05/10)
